{m}>0.1$ and\n$2.5\\%$ having $e_\\mathrm{m}>0.9$), and the final BH spin axis tends to be\nrandomly orientated. Measurements or constraints on eccentric mergers and\n$\\theta_\\rm {sl}^\\rm f$ from LIGO/VIRGO and LISA would provide useful\ndiagnostics on the dynamical formation of merging BH or NS binaries in triples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 May 2019 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 12 Aug 2019 18:21:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
