unded base flow including its transients. The results are\ncompared with the inertial wave part of the DNS (the so called \"filtered DNS\"\nor simply \"FNS\"), for which the agreement is excellent and accounts for minor\ndiscrepancies evident in the Part I results for the QG-trigger.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 May 2019 20:32:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-05-03"}
